    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Moldings which are nailed, laid on, or otherwise fastened to the work rather than cut into the solid material.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000018341/Harris, Historic Architecture Sourcebook (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Molduras las cuales son clavadas, puestas en, o de otra forma sujetas a una obra más que cortada en un material sólido.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
